---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Cookie Policy - BitcoinForWifi">
	<section class="py-20">
		<div class="container mx-auto px-4">
			<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
				<div class="text-center mb-16">
					<h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-6">
						<span class="gradient-text">Cookie Policy</span>
					</h1>
					<p class="text-gray-300 text-lg">
						Last updated: {new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' })}
					</p>
				</div>

				<div class="prose prose-lg prose-invert max-w-none">
					<h2>What Are Cookies</h2>
					<p>
						Cookies are small text files that are stored on your device (computer, tablet, or mobile) when you visit a website. They are widely used to make websites work more efficiently and to provide information to website owners.
					</p>
					<p>
						Cookies allow us to recognize you when you return to our website, remember your preferences, and provide a personalized experience. This Cookie Policy explains how BitcoinForWifi uses cookies and similar tracking technologies.
					</p>

					<h2>How We Use Cookies</h2>
					<p>
						We use cookies for several purposes to enhance your experience on our website:
					</p>
					<ul>
						<li><strong>Essential Cookies:</strong> Required for basic website functionality</li>
						<li><strong>Performance Cookies:</strong> Help us understand how visitors interact with our site</li>
						<li><strong>Functional Cookies:</strong> Remember your preferences and settings</li>
						<li><strong>Targeting Cookies:</strong> Used to deliver relevant content and advertisements</li>
						<li><strong>Social Media Cookies:</strong> Enable social media sharing and integration</li>
					</ul>

					<h2>Types of Cookies We Use</h2>
					
					<h3>Essential Cookies</h3>
					<p>These cookies are necessary for our website to function properly. They enable basic functions like page navigation, access to secure areas, and authentication. Without these cookies, the website cannot operate correctly.</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Session management and user authentication</li>
						<li>Security and fraud prevention</li>
						<li>Load balancing and server management</li>
					</ul>

					<h3>Performance and Analytics Cookies</h3>
					<p>These cookies help us understand how visitors interact with our website by collecting and reporting information anonymously. This information helps us improve the performance and user experience of our site.</p>
					<ul>
						<li><strong>Google Analytics:</strong> Tracks website usage and provides statistical data</li>
						<li><strong>Hotjar:</strong> Records user sessions and provides heatmaps</li>
						<li><strong>Custom analytics:</strong> Internal tracking for performance optimization</li>
					</ul>

					<h3>Functional Cookies</h3>
					<p>These cookies allow our website to remember choices you make and provide enhanced, more personal features. They may be set by us or by third-party providers whose services we have added to our pages.</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Remembering your language preferences</li>
						<li>Saving your newsletter subscription status</li>
						<li>Customizing content based on your interests</li>
						<li>Remembering your cookie consent preferences</li>
					</ul>

					<h3>Targeting and Advertising Cookies</h3>
					<p>These cookies are used to deliver advertisements that are relevant to you and your interests. They are also used to limit the number of times you see an advertisement and help measure the effectiveness of advertising campaigns.</p>
					<ul>
						<li><strong>Google AdSense:</strong> Displays relevant advertisements</li>
						<li><strong>Facebook Pixel:</strong> Tracks ad conversions and retargeting</li>
						<li><strong>Twitter Ads:</strong> Enables targeted advertising on Twitter</li>
					</ul>

					<h3>Social Media Cookies</h3>
					<p>These cookies enable social media functionality and integration with social platforms. They may be used to share content on social media or to track your activity across different websites.</p>
					<ul>
						<li><strong>Facebook:</strong> Like, share, and comment functionality</li>
						<li><strong>Twitter:</strong> Tweet and follow buttons</li>
						<li><strong>LinkedIn:</strong> Professional sharing and networking</li>
						<li><strong>Reddit:</strong> Content sharing and voting</li>
					</ul>

					<h2>Third-Party Cookies</h2>
					<p>
						Our website uses various third-party services that may place cookies on your device. These third-party services have their own privacy policies and cookie policies, and we are not responsible for their practices.
					</p>
					
					<h3>Analytics Services</h3>
					<ul>
						<li><strong>Google Analytics:</strong> Web analytics and user behavior tracking</li>
						<li><strong>Google Tag Manager:</strong> Manages tracking tags and scripts</li>
					</ul>

					<h3>Advertising Networks</h3>
					<ul>
						<li><strong>Google AdSense:</strong> Display advertising and revenue generation</li>
						<li><strong>Google Ad Manager:</strong> Ad serving and management</li>
					</ul>

					<h3>Social Media Platforms</h3>
					<ul>
						<li><strong>Meta (Facebook/Instagram):</strong> Social sharing and analytics</li>
						<li><strong>Twitter/X:</strong> Content sharing and engagement tracking</li>
						<li><strong>LinkedIn:</strong> Professional networking and content sharing</li>
					</ul>

					<h2>Cookie Duration</h2>
					<p>Cookies have different lifespans depending on their purpose:</p>
					
					<h3>Session Cookies</h3>
					<p>These cookies are temporary and are deleted when you close your browser. They are used for:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Maintaining your session while you navigate the site</li>
						<li>Tracking your progress through multi-step processes</li>
						<li>Security verification during your visit</li>
					</ul>

					<h3>Persistent Cookies</h3>
					<p>These cookies remain on your device for a specified period or until you delete them. They are used for:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Remembering your preferences across sessions</li>
						<li>Tracking your long-term usage patterns</li>
						<li>Maintaining your authentication status</li>
						<li>Personalizing content based on past behavior</li>
					</ul>

					<h2>Managing Your Cookie Preferences</h2>
					<p>You have several options for managing cookies:</p>
					
					<h3>Browser Settings</h3>
					<p>Most browsers allow you to control cookies through their settings:</p>
					<ul>
						<li><strong>Accept all cookies:</strong> Allow all types of cookies</li>
						<li><strong>Reject all cookies:</strong> Block all cookies (may affect website functionality)</li>
						<li><strong>Block third-party cookies:</strong> Only allow first-party cookies</li>
						<li><strong>Delete cookies:</strong> Remove existing cookies from your device</li>
					</ul>

					<h3>Browser-Specific Instructions</h3>
					<ul>
						<li><strong>Chrome:</strong> Settings → Privacy and security → Cookies and other site data</li>
						<li><strong>Firefox:</strong> Options → Privacy & Security → Cookies and Site Data</li>
						<li><strong>Safari:</strong> Preferences → Privacy → Cookies and website data</li>
						<li><strong>Edge:</strong> Settings → Privacy, search, and services → Cookies</li>
					</ul>

					<h3>Our Cookie Consent Banner</h3>
					<p>
						When you first visit our website, you'll see a cookie consent banner that allows you to:
					</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Accept all cookies</li>
						<li>Reject non-essential cookies</li>
						<li>Customize your cookie preferences</li>
						<li>Change your preferences at any time</li>
					</ul>

					<h2>Cookie Consent and GDPR</h2>
					<p>
						We comply with the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) and other applicable privacy laws. This means:
					</p>
					<ul>
						<li>We obtain your consent before placing non-essential cookies</li>
						<li>We provide clear information about our cookie usage</li>
						<li>We allow you to withdraw consent at any time</li>
						<li>We maintain records of your consent preferences</li>
					</ul>

					<h2>Impact of Disabling Cookies</h2>
					<p>Disabling cookies may affect your experience on our website:</p>
					
					<h3>Essential Cookies</h3>
					<p>If you disable essential cookies, some features of our website may not work properly, including:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Secure login and authentication</li>
						<li>Shopping cart functionality (if applicable)</li>
						<li>Personalized content delivery</li>
					</ul>

					<h3>Non-Essential Cookies</h3>
					<p>If you disable non-essential cookies, you may experience:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Less personalized content and recommendations</li>
						<li>Repetitive advertisements</li>
						<li>Inability to use social media sharing features</li>
						<li>Reduced website performance optimization</li>
					</ul>

					<h2>Cookie Updates and Changes</h2>
					<p>
						We may update this Cookie Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our use of cookies or applicable laws. Any changes will be posted on this page with an updated "Last updated" date.
					</p>
					<p>
						We encourage you to review this Cookie Policy periodically to stay informed about our use of cookies and how you can manage your preferences.
					</p>

					<h2>International Data Transfers</h2>
					<p>
						Some of our third-party service providers are located outside your country. By using our website, you consent to the transfer of your data to these countries for the purposes described in this policy.
					</p>
					<p>
						We ensure that all third-party providers offer adequate protection for your personal data in accordance with applicable data protection laws.
					</p>

					<h2>Your Rights</h2>
					<p>Depending on your location, you may have the following rights regarding cookies:</p>
					<ul>
						<li><strong>Right to Information:</strong> Know what cookies we use and why</li>
						<li><strong>Right to Consent:</strong> Choose which cookies to accept</li>
						<li><strong>Right to Withdraw:</strong> Change your cookie preferences at any time</li>
						<li><strong>Right to Object:</strong> Object to certain types of cookies</li>
						<li><strong>Right to Erasure:</strong> Request deletion of your data</li>
					</ul>

					<h2>Contact Information</h2>
					<p>
						If you have any questions about this Cookie Policy or how we use cookies, please contact us:
					</p>
					<ul>
						<li>By email: privacy@bitcoinblog.com</li>
						<li>By visiting this page on our website: bitcoinblog.com/contact</li>
						<li>By mail: [Your Company Address]</li>
					</ul>

					<div class="bg-bitcoin-orange/20 border border-bitcoin-orange rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
						<h3 class="text-bitcoin-orange font-bold text-lg mb-3">🍪 QUICK REFERENCE</h3>
						<div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-gray-300">
							<div>
								<h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">Essential Cookies:</h4>
								<p class="text-sm">Required for basic functionality. Cannot be disabled.</p>
							</div>
							<div>
								<h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">Analytics Cookies:</h4>
								<p class="text-sm">Help us improve our website. Can be disabled.</p>
							</div>
							<div>
								<h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">Functional Cookies:</h4>
								<p class="text-sm">Enhance your experience. Can be disabled.</p>
							</div>
							<div>
								<h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">Advertising Cookies:</h4>
								<p class="text-sm">Show relevant ads. Can be disabled.</p>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>
